  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Abatacept disrupts T-cell coactivation signals in rheumatoid arthritis (RA). Its potential
      effects on B cells are not well described. This study will assess the effects of abatacept
      therapy on the phenotype and function of peripheral blood B cells in patients with RA.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
